Rating: 4
These are so worth the effort and expense. Do yourself a favor and a) don't chill the dough for longer than 45 (I'd do 35 min or less), as the dough becomes ROCK hard and so difficult to work with; and b) use a #16 ice cream scoop (that's about 1/3 C.) to scoop these cookies, then smoosh them down by a goodly amount before baking. I've made them several times and now chill the dough for about 1/2 hour then portion out the dough on the cookie sheet (it makes exactly 18) and bake them in the next day or so (wrap the sheet so they don't dry out). I'd think that you could even freeze the dough as individual cookie "pucks" and bake as needed (trust me, after you try these, you will absolutely NEED them) for about 19 minutes. You could even add about 1/2 C. more walnuts.

