Excellent cookies but quite prone to burning on the bottoms if you a) do not use parchment paper and b) do not watch them closely. Lack of parchment paper caused smoke to pour out of my oven! With parchment paper, however, these came out perfectly. Also, use 6 (not 5) Heath bars and chop them into slightly larger pieces (I aimed for the size of one chocolate chip but next time will aim for the size of approximately three chocolate chips.) Their flavor gets lost a bit, otherwise. Lengthy refrigeration makes the dough very tough (a sturdy ice cream scoop helped me, although next time I'll try rolling the dough into a log first, as suggested in another helpful review.) Finally, instead of super-sizing I made these into about 50 smaller cookies. They took 13 minutes to come out moist and burn-free! Delicious!

