These are not for the faint of heart! Using a quality chocolate would be a must in my opinion; not Hershey's chocolate chips. I doubled the recipe and added a few more Tbsp of flour plus a small amount of cinnamon. Heath bars in chunks seems much better than the small heath chips. Baked on parchment (wax paper sounded so odd) without any sticking at all. Cookies don't flatten out as much as the picture shows, but perhaps that is because I put these in the garage to cool overnight (ran out of time) and the dough is quite solid and cumbersome to spoon out of the bowl. Next time, I'll chill for the 2 hours. There will be a next time! I wish I had made 1/2 without nuts so those who don't eat nuts could enjoy.

