This recipe was fantastic! I made a few small changes. I doubled the recipe to make the cookies for a work function. I used bags of chocolate-covered Heath bits, and used 3 for the double recipe instead of two, but omitted nuts. I let the dough chill for about two hours. The double recipe yielded about 45 large cookies and 10 small. The cookies burnt a bit on the bottom, so I reduced the cooking time to 13.5 minutes, and they turned out perfectly. They taste a lot like brownies, which are one of my favorite desserts, so I loved them. The cookies were a huge hit with everyone else, and I will definitely keep this recipe!

