Rating: 4
These were fabulous. I made them with Lindt bittersweet chocolate. I've made them twice--the first time I subbed pecans for the walnuts and didn't cook them as long; both mistakes. The slight astringency of the walnuts is needed to contrast with the chocolate, and they do need to be dry on top or they are unappealingly uncooked in the middle. Both times I made them with a bag of Heath bits, and next time I will either add two bags to punch up the toffee flavor, or I will chop the candy bars. I think that larger chunks of toffee would make for a better cookie. I also added milk chocolate chips the second time and loved the contrast with the very bittersweet chocolate. These are still crunchy on the outside, chewy on the inside two days later--a real winner! Lastly, I ran out of parchment and used waxed paper as the recipe suggested. Big mistake--now I have wax all over my baking sheet and I'm having trouble getting it off.

