Rating: 4
I have made these cookies at least a dozen times, always to rave reviews. My family call them "crack" cookies because they're so addictive. Some tips that I hope are helpful: I use a stand mixer and beat the eggs and sugar until thick and light lemon colored ; this usually takes longer than 5 minutes and seems to be the key to the cookies turning out properly. I use parchement paper to bake them on and let them cool slightly on the baking sheet before moving them. Sometimes they require more than the 45 minute chill time in the fridge before baking. Give these cookies a chance, they're terrific.

