Made these over the weekend. Turned out great - in taste and presentation. I baked them on Reynolds Release foil and didn't have any problems with sticking as others have noted. I think one of the tricks with this recipe is making sure that the dough is well chilled before baking. My kitchen was warm when I scooped these onto the cookie sheet, so I put the entire sheet with the dough balls back in the fridge for a while to chill again. The result was prefectly shaped cookies. Next time, I would probably add more walnuts and maybe even more toffee. I did use crushed toffee bars, but would probably just use the Heath bits in the baking aisle next time. Great recipe - a keeper!

