These cookies are delicious and have universal appeal - the best of both brownies and cookies. I used semi- sweet chocolate and Muscovado sugar, and no walnuts because I didn't have any. The Muscovado with the toffee and rich chocolate was phenomenal, so if you can find it and don't mind the expense, substituting it for the regular brown sugar is a really easy way to fancy up these homey (decadent) cookies. I recommend keeping the toffee in biggish chunks, and not omitting some kind of nut. The cookies were excellent without them, but the added textural interest would have been welcome.

