OUTSTANDING. I used all bittersweet chocolate (ghirardelli), reduced the sugar by I think 1/4 cup, beat the eggs and sugar for 6 minutes, and chilled overnight. I think those last two are responsible for the incredible texture of these cookies - they are rich and soft like a brownie, but surprisingly light. I also used one more toffee bar than recommended, and I think I will use more next time (and there WILL be a next time). I didn't toast the walnuts this time, but I think I will next time, as the toasty flavor will compliment the chocolate very nicely. I made them a little smaller - maybe 2 tbsp each, ish? - so I ended up with 36, and baked each batch for 13 minutes. They were a BIG hit, and I will definitely be making them again!

