I had to make these cookies just because they got so many fantastic reviews. I agree. These were so chocolatey-decadent! I read a lot of the reviews before making and took some of the suggestions. I used 12 oz. bittersweet chocolate and 4 oz. unsweetened. I beat the eggs and sugar for somewhere between 5 and 7 minutes. I melted the butter and chocolate in the microwave. I omitted the nuts, just as personal choice, and broke the toffee bars into larger chunks. I did refrigerate the dough overnight, and I think that really helped them turn out wonderfully. The dough was really hard from the overnight chill, so I shaped the cookies with my hands a bit (I got 20 cookies), baked them at 350 on parchment-lined sheets for exactly 15 minutes and they were perfect. Still soft in the middle -- delicious! Husband LOVED them, and he already wants to know when I will make them again even though they're not all gone yet!

