Rating: 4
Outstanding recipe - a real crowd-pleaser. Be sure to chill the dough for a full 45 minutes, even longer if your mixing bowl is small & deep. Let the cookies cool fully on the baking sheet before removing. They are gooey/fragile, and will smoosh up if you try to remove them too soon. I used silpat sheets on my cookie sheets, with excellent results. As the other reviews noted, the quality of chocolate will make or break this recipe.

