Based on other reviews, I made these cookies verrrrry carefully: measured exactly and used 1 lb. Scharffenberger bittersweet chocolate, mixed the sugar and eggs for 7 minutes, used eggs at room temperature, chilled for 2 hours (dough was extremely stiff by this point), baked for 15 minutes exactly. Used a 2 T cookie scoop, gave up because of the stickyness and dropped about 2 T by hand on parchment. Cookies came out beautifully and looked like the photo. Very good warm, excellent cold. Will definitely make again!!

