I have to admit, I was skeptical about making these cookies based on the vast difference in opinions regarding the recipe and its results. However, I read all of the reviews and took the general consensus. I have to go with the majority here, these cookies are fabulous and I had absolutely no problems making them. I followed the reciped as stated making sure to mix the brown sugar eggs for the full 5 minutes, chilling the dough until firm (which was key because based on the consistency of the dough after mixing, which was like a brownie mix,I thought I had done something wrong), and then using the parchment paper and allowing them to cool before attempting to remove them. For the people who had trouble with this recipe, I must agree with prior comments, you probably did something wrong. For anyone having trouble finding bittersweet chocolate, Ghiradelli makes "double chocolate" chocolate chips, which if you read the ingredients, you will see they are made from bittersweet chocolate. So, for those of you who are skeptical, don't be, these are soft, fudgey, rich, great tasting cookies that are worth the effort and expense.

