Rating: 3
I've made these cookies a couple of times, and there are a couple of small changes I've made that seem to really help. First of all, the Hershey's Bake Shop line makes a 7 oz. bag of chocolate-covered toffee bits that work really well. Maybe the most important change is to NOT chill the batter for 45 minutes. I did that once, and the cookies came out like flat, crispy disks -- okay if that's the cookie you're looking for, but if you want something more brownie-like, just chill the batter until slightly thickened, 5-10 minutes. Don't even bother using parchment or wax paper -- just lightly grease a baking sheet and drop the cookies onto that. It's a very rich cookie, but has been popular at gatherings I've brought it to.

