Rating: 4
Loved these cookies! But I rearranged the instructions a bit (kind of by mistake, but it worked out): I took dry ingredients and put them in my KitchenAid mixer, then added the butter (softened) and whisked it all together with the brown sugar, vanilla, and eggs (for 5 minutes). Then I melted the chocolate and Heath pieces together in a big bowl over a double-boiler, then added that to the whisking mixture, and then added the walnuts. I didn't have to wait 45 minutes for the batter to refrigerate before baking the cookies... only waited about 10 minutes. Baked the cookies at 350 for 15-17 minutes and they're PERFECT. I will make these again tonight.

