Rating: 4
I've made this recipe 5 times and have gotten rave reviews each time. Tips are to use 1 cup flour and substitute 4 oz of unsweetened chocolate for that amount of bittersweet. Cookies will be puffy and not as sweet. For one batch that I brought to a picnic I added 3/4 tsp of cayenne pepper. Besides giving some zip to the chocolate-sweetness, it definitely increased the consumption of the home brewed stout!

