Rating: 4
These cookies have become a family favorite. Absolutely scrumptious! They are, however, quite rich so I make them a bit smaller than recommended. I substituted Hershey toffee pieces for the Heath bar and find it works very well. I've noticed in reading other reviews that many people have had difficulty in preparing this recipe. All I can say is, use the best quality chocolate you can find (I used Ghiradelli bittersweet) and follow the directions i.e., beat the sugar for 5 minutes until thick, refrigerate the batter for 45 minutes before baking, use parchment paper, and cook for the designated amount of time. This is not one of those recipes you can "fudge" on. Follow the directions and you're sure to have satisfying results.

