Rating: 0
To the cook from Laguna Niguel, CA. Perhaps you didn't scorch your chocolate. Its important in a recipe with such a huge amount to use a brand that tastes good. Chocolates vary enormously in flavour. The Baker's Catalog has a good selection & describes the flavours accurately. You can 'toughen' chocolate & spoil its flavour & texture by accidentally splashing water (even a tiny amount will do it) into the chocolate mixture as you melt it over the double-boiler.

