Rating: 3
For weeks I have been trying to get a co-worker to visit the Epicurious website, and when I brought these cookies to an office lunch, she was finally compelled to take a look! I did not use a double boiler to melt the chocolate and the butter; instead I melted them in the microwave on high for about 2 1/2 minutes, checking every 45 seconds or so to stir and to make sure the mixture did not burn. When most of the chocolate and butter had melted, I removed the bowl from the microwave and stirred the mixture until smooth. I am a huge fan of cookie dough and am often disappointed when the dough becomes a cookie, but that was not the case with these cookies. The dough was so delectable, almost like fudge, that I was certain the cookies could not possibly measure up to the taste, but, much to my surprise and delight, they did. The batter yielded 22 cookies and that was even after I'd consumed a considerable amount of the chilled dough! Several people asked for the recipe and there was not a single cookie left to take home with me!

Rating: 4
These cookies are one of the few that actually taste better the next day. For even more decadence I added an extra chocolate bar and substituted pecans for the walnuts. These are our new favorite cookies.

